 coefficients ${\\rm Re}(C_9)$ and ${\\rm Re}(C_{10})$ from\n$B\\to\\pi\\mu^+\\mu^-$ and $B\\to K\\mu^+\\mu^-$ are competitive with those from\n$B\\to K^* \\mu^+\\mu^-$, and display a 2.0$\\sigma$ tension with the Standard\nModel. Our predictions for $B\\to K(\\pi)\\nu\\bar\\nu$ and $B\\to\\pi\\tau\\nu$ are\nclose to the current experimental limits.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Oct 2015 14:56:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 22 Oct 2015 21:02:53 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 12 Feb 2016 22:14:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-02-16"}
